{"batch":"Cross-cutting Sweep","batch_index":2,"assessments":{"api_surface_coherence":79.0,"contract_coherence":76.0,"error_consistency":74.0},"dimension_notes":{"api_surface_coherence":{"evidence":["Publishing APIs use different failure contracts for similar queue/bus operations: `EventBroker.Publish*` returns explicit backpressure/cancel errors, while `LogstreamRuntime.PublishSystemLog` is fire-and-forget with no return channel for failure (`goseg/docker/events/events.go`, `goseg/session/logstream_session_store.go`).","Runtime APIs in adjacent subsystems expose inconsistent nil/missing-dependency behavior: some methods return typed dependency errors, others silently succeed/no-op (`goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_core.go`, `goseg/broadcast/state.go`).","WiFi query APIs return usable results plus non-nil warning errors in some paths, but this mixed contract is not uniformly normalized by callers (`goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go`, `goseg/system/wifi_test.go`)."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"},"contract_coherence":{"evidence":["`StartupRuntime.Initialize()` returns `nil` when callback is unset, while sibling startup methods (`LoadWireguard`, `LoadMC`, `LoadUrbits`, etc.) return explicit missing-dependency errors, so the same runtime contract class has divergent semantics (`goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_core.go`).","`broadcastStateRuntime` methods mix nil-receiver semantics (silent no-op/zero return in `UpdateBroadcast`/`GetState`) with hard errors in `UpdateScheduledPack`/`PublishSchedulePack`, making precondition contracts non-uniform (`goseg/broadcast/state.go`).","WiFi methods expose a dual-result contract (data + warning error) that is only partially honored by internal callers: `primaryWifiDevice` downgrades partial parse errors, but `listSSIDs` forwards raw warning errors unchanged (`goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go`, `goseg/system/wifi_test.go`)."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"},"error_consistency":{"evidence":["Backpressure/error propagation is explicit in event publishing (`ErrTransitionBusFull`, `ErrTransitionPublishTimeout`) but absent in system log publishing (`PublishSystemLog` has no error return despite asynchronous bus semantics), creating inconsistent failure visibility for queue-based operations (`goseg/docker/events/events.go`, `goseg/session/logstream_session_store.go`, `goseg/logger/logger_test.go`).","Config patch parsing mixes strict concrete-type assertions (`parseSessionMap`, `parseDiskWarningMap`) with tolerant JSON re-decode parsing (`parseLinuxUpdatesValue`, `parsePenpaiModels`) inside the same `map[string]interface{}` patch pipeline, producing inconsistent parse error behavior for similarly sourced payloads (`goseg/config/config_update_schema.go`).","WiFi parsing uses partial-parse warnings as `error` while still returning data, but higher-level method handling is inconsistent, so equivalent malformed-input cases can either continue or fail depending on call path (`goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go`, `goseg/system/wifi_test.go`)."],"impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"}},"findings":[{"dimension":"contract_coherence","identifier":"runtime_nil_contract_divergence","summary":"Runtime dependency methods use conflicting nil/missing-callback contracts (silent success vs explicit error) within the same API families.","related_files":["goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_core.go","goseg/broadcast/state.go","goseg/session/logstream_session_store.go"],"evidence":["`StartupRuntime.Initialize()` returns `nil` when `InitializeFn` is unset, but sibling methods return `seams.MissingRuntimeDependency(...)` on unset callbacks.","`broadcastStateRuntime` nil receiver returns zero/no-op for `GetState` and `UpdateBroadcast`, but returns `errBroadcastRuntimeRequired` for `UpdateScheduledPack` and `PublishSchedulePack`.","`logstreamSessionStore` methods uniformly no-op on nil receiver, including mutating/publishing paths, with no error path available."],"suggestion":"Define and enforce one runtime precondition policy per API family (either explicit dependency errors or documented no-op semantics), then normalize all methods to that policy and add contract tests for nil/missing dependency behavior.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"implicit_runtime_precondition_policy"},{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"async_publish_failure_visibility_mismatch","summary":"Asynchronous publish paths expose backpressure/cancellation errors inconsistently across subsystems.","related_files":["goseg/docker/events/events.go","goseg/session/logstream_session_store.go","goseg/logger/logger_test.go"],"evidence":["`publishDropOnFull` returns `ErrTransitionBusFull` and `ErrTransitionPublishTimeout`, giving callers deterministic queue failure signals.","`LogstreamRuntime.PublishSystemLog` returns no error and `logstreamSessionStore.PublishSystemLog` unconditionally publishes with no propagation path.","Logger sink contract in tests (`testSystemLogSink.PublishSystemLog`) assumes fire-and-forget semantics, reinforcing a non-reporting error strategy unlike event publishing."],"suggestion":"Standardize async publish interfaces around an explicit result contract (e.g., `error` with shared sentinel errors for full/cancelled/not-initialized), or define a single explicit best-effort policy and remove/encapsulate conflicting strict error semantics behind dedicated adapters.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"inconsistent_async_bus_contracts"},{"dimension":"api_surface_coherence","identifier":"partial_result_error_contract_is_nonuniform","summary":"WiFi API methods expose partial data plus warning errors, but callers and sibling methods do not apply a consistent handling strategy.","related_files":["goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go","goseg/system/wifi_test.go"],"evidence":["`parseNmcliWifiDeviceRecords` and `parseNmcliWifiScanResults` can return populated results with `wifiNmcliPartialParseError`.","`primaryWifiDevice` explicitly downgrades partial parse errors when at least one device exists, while `listSSIDs` directly returns `(ssids, err)` and leaves policy to callers.","Tests encode this dual contract (`wifiDevices` and `listSSIDs` expect non-empty results with non-nil partial-parse errors), indicating a deliberately mixed but hard-to-predict API shape."],"suggestion":"Introduce a single typed partial-result abstraction (for example `{Data, Warnings}` or a dedicated warning channel/type) and apply it consistently across `wifiDevices`, `listSSIDs`, and upstream call sites so callers do not need method-specific error interpretation.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"partial_success_model_drift"},{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"config_patch_parser_type_tolerance_drift","summary":"Config patch parsing applies inconsistent type-tolerance rules for values from the same `map[string]interface{}` boundary.","related_files":["goseg/config/config_update_schema.go","goseg/config/config_test.go"],"evidence":["`buildConfigPatch` ingests `map[string]interface{}` values, but `parseSessionMap`/`parseDiskWarningMap` require concrete map types (`map[string]structs.SessionInfo` / `map[string]structs.DiskWarning`).","In the same parser layer, `parseLinuxUpdatesValue` and `parsePenpaiModels` normalize generic inputs by marshal/unmarshal, accepting structurally compatible untyped maps/slices.","Existing tests heavily validate merge behavior but do not provide equivalent boundary tests for generic map-backed session/disk-warning patches, leaving this inconsistency unguarded."],"suggestion":"Unify parser strategy at this boundary: either require strict typed option builders before `buildConfigPatch`, or make all composite-field parsers normalize generic map input through shared decode helpers; add tests that feed untyped JSON-decoded maps for every composite patch key.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"boundary_decode_policy_inconsistency"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Implicit and undocumented runtime precondition policy leads to divergent nil/missing-dependency semantics across similarly shaped APIs.","Queue-based async interfaces evolved with different reliability assumptions (strict erroring vs best-effort fire-and-forget) without a common contract layer.","Boundary parsing rules were implemented per-field rather than from a single decode policy, creating tolerance drift within one patch pipeline."],"likely_symptoms":["runtime_nil_contract_divergence","async_publish_failure_visibility_mismatch","partial_result_error_contract_is_nonuniform","config_patch_parser_type_tolerance_drift"],"possible_false_positives":[]}}
